    intensity = generate_feature('intensity', target_values=[energy, pulse_width])  # Simplified; in a realistic model, we would consider covariance with 'pulse_width' and other features here

    cutoff_energy = energy * covariance / intensity[i % len(target_thickness)] if feature_name == 'target_thickness' else np.repeat(np.mean([6.23e13]), size=1)[0]  # Simplified, normally more complex
